history: speaker1: Hello.
speaker2: Hello. Do you have a favorite genre of music?
speaker1: No I'm more of an outdoors type person, with nature.
speaker2: Ah what do you like doing outdoors?
speaker1: Running, camping, hiking with my dog. What are some of your hobbies?
speaker2: Cool. I like watching movies and hanging with my kids.
speaker1: Do you prefer coffee or tea?
speaker2: Hmm I don't have a preference. Do you?
speaker1: Yes coffee, love trying new coffees and ways to brew them.
speaker2: What's your favorite coffee brew?
speaker1: Blonde roast, starbucks brand brew is my favorite.
speaker2: Ah cool! I like starbucks coffee.
speaker1: I took my dog to the Starbucks drive-thru.
speaker2: How was your coffee?  Do they have blonde roast there?  What kind do you usually get?
speaker1: It was pretty tasty! My dog sure was popular, lol.  I love their blonde roast but went for a caramel macchiatto today
speaker2: I see.  I love the caramel macchiatto.  Do you have a way to make coffee when you are doing events outdoors?
speaker1: I have a little camp coffee pot, just pour boiling water from the fire over the grounds. It's quite wonderful at sunrise.  Have you ever been able to take your kids camping?

speaker2: Yes.  Well, we have a camper so it's not 'roughing it'.  But we do like getting out in nature.  They love it.  And, to me, nothing is better than watching the sunrise with a cup of coffee in your hand.
speaker1: Oh I bet having a camper is so nice! It's one of our savings goals. I do love the idea of having a toilet and shower easily accessible!

speaker2: It is wonderful.  And it allows us to stay longer than we would in a tent.  I especially love it because, at night, we pull the screen and projector out and watch movies outside with some popcorn.  As my friend says, its more like 'glamping'.
speaker1: That actually sounds wonderful. I do love camping but I'm getting older and sleeping on the ground is starting to be a little ridiculous. Glamping through my 40s would probably save my back
speaker2: I am sure.  but with your running and outdoor lifestyle I am sure you are still in great shape?
speaker1: I do my best to keep in shape, not perfect but I do try. I like to think the outdoors has kept me young!

speaker2: I can only imagine.  Having a camper would definitely give your body ample rest during all your outdoor activities.  I love to run also.  But it is nice to have a comfortable bed to sleep in afterward.

speaker1: I heard from a friend a couple of days ago that they were planning on selling their camper, and I thought you might be interested in buying it off from them. I can give you their cell, so you can give them a call and negotiate the price.
response: I might be! Do you happene to have any more information about it right now? Hey, maybe then I could sell you mine and we could be glamping buddies! It would certainly be better for your back and I would have an adult to talk to instead of just the kids.
entities: I like watching movies and hanging with my kids.
Glamping through my 40s would probably save my back

speaker1: That's cool. Are you a stay at home mom or do you also have a job?
speaker2: Just a stay at home mom..
speaker1: Nice, I am a plumber on the side!
speaker2: I'm sure that can be a dirty job at times, just like a mom. Lol.
speaker1: Ha you are right!.
speaker2: Do you live in the states? I live in california..

speaker1: I just saw the greatest sunset so far this year. I know you like movies more than sunsets, but I heard there are supposed to be some great sunsets this week and I figured I should let you know that there may be some great ones.

speaker2: I do like movies quite a bit, but I don't mind sunsets at all. After all, there are great sunsets where I live in California. Sometimes, you'll have the entire evening sky in shades of orange and violet. It's stunning.
speaker1: I bet they are gorgeous on the west coast, I hope I get to see one someday. How are your kids doing?
speaker2: My kids are doing great. Speaking of sunsets, maybe we can watch sunsets together instead of movies. I imagine that'll be better for our eyes.
speaker1: I bet they would love that, especially if you can find a beach. Do they like to swim?

speaker2: I do. Water is quite relaxing. I find the sensation of being in water to be therapeutic. I have to say, however, that I'm not as big of a fan of the beach. Sand gets everywhere and it's hard to clean. My kids love it, though, and for that reason, I oblige.
speaker1: I am with you, I do not like the sand at all but the beach is my favorite place to watch sunsets. Have you watched any good movies with your kids lateley?

speaker2: Haha, 'good' as in movies I like, or movies they like? We've watched a lot of movies they like for sure, or in other words, every Disney movie under the sun. Don't get me wrong, though--a good many Disney movies are excellent!
speaker1: They are good, what types of movies do you prefer?
speaker2: I like sloppy romance movies (which I imagine my kids would dislike). I'm also up for the occasional horror movie, but again, my kids definitely aren't interested in that.
speaker1: It sounds like Disney suits them just right then! Are your kids in school?
speaker2: They are, which basically means I've got a good portion of the day to myself.
speaker1: I just got confirmation on a 'Hawaii Sunset' tour I booked for next month!
speaker2: That sounds right up your alley! I am sure you will love it. Have you ever done a sunset tour before?
speaker1: First time! Surprising, right? God I am so excited!
speaker2: Good for you! I am sure it will be the trip of a lifetime! You will have to send me pictures so I can share them with my kids!
speaker1: I will! I wish you guys could come with but I know it would be a hassle because of school. I'll think of some way to treat you all when I return.
speaker2: That would be so nice of you! Was it hard for you to get time off for your trip?
speaker1: My pleasure! Yeah, imagine that. Working two jobs and struggling to make time for myself. I imagine it's the kind of the same for you being home with the kids most of the time.

speaker2: I could imagine it was hard to schedule the trip, but you deserve the time and it will be worth it. Yes, taking time for myself is nearly impossible. I swear I am busier as a stay at home mom than I ever was working. But I just remind myself, the kids are only young once and I will thank myself later for being there.
speaker1: I bet. That's sweet. You have to make the most out of every moment. I learned that from watching sunsets.
speaker2: That is probably why I love romance movies, much like you love sunsets. The movie is my small escape into a new and exciting world.

speaker1: Sometimes we all need a little escape. You deserve that freedom too. It has to be stressful handling your kids and partner all the time. It must feel like it never stops being your responsibility.
speaker2: It often does feel like a 24/7 job. Not that I am complaining about it totally. It is also very rewarding. But since you have 2 jobs, I am sure you feel just as exhausted.
speaker1: Have you seen any new romance movies lately?
speaker2: I haven't, my family has been so busy that I have not had a minute to sit and relax. Have you seen any new Disney movies recently?
speaker1: Yes, I have seen a new Disney movie lately it is called Luca. Have you seen it?
speaker2: No, I haven't. I did see that my kids were watching it the other day and they said it was really good. Did you like it?
speaker1: It was a really good movie. Really cute movie. I enjoyed watching it. What Disney movies have you seen lately?
speaker2: I haven't had a lot of time for movies lately but the last Disney movie we watched as a family was Miracle, my husband really enjoys the Disney sports movies.
speaker1: I have never heard of the Miracle movie what is that about? I like watching the sport movies on Disney also.
speaker2: It is about the1980 U.S. men's Olympic hockey team, it is a really good movie. I would totally recommend that you watch it!
speaker1: Okay, that does sound like a good movie. Do you know where I can find it to watch it?
speaker2: Do you have Disney Plus? If so it is on there!
speaker1: Yes, I do have Disney Plus. I will have to check the movie out.
response: Remember the Titans is another great movie that is on the Disney Plus app.
entities: Yes, I do have Disney Plus. I will have to check the movie out.

history: speaker1: My father was a farmer when I was a boy, and my two older brothers helped on the farm.
speaker2: My father was a hunter and has passed down hunting to me. I enjoy going hunting any chance I get. What was your favorite thing on the farm?.
speaker1: I loved playing in the grain silo (carefully) with my brothers noah and tasha.
speaker2: Oh my.. That sounds like it could be dangerous.
speaker1: Tasha always made sure the grain couldn't fall on us!
speaker2: I see. Did you have a favorite animal on the farm?.
speaker1: My cat sonny was a favorite. He is still alive.
speaker2: Aww that's really cute. I love cats too.
speaker1: He might come visit me in kansas city where I just moved.
speaker2: How is the weather in kansas city?.
speaker1: It's still cold here but the spring flowers are beginning to bud.
speaker2: Same here in pennsylvania. I cannot wait for it to be warm all the time..
speaker1: Are you planning on going hunting anytime soon?
speaker2: I will once it warms up a little bit. In the meantime, I will stay home with my cat and watch some tv.
speaker1: Cool.  Sonny and I like to watch tv too.  So, what kind of hunting are you planning to do when it gets warmer?
speaker2: Probably deer, that's the animal my dad taught me to hunt the most. Have you ever been hunting for deer?
speaker1: No, I've always been too busy with the farm and all to do something like that.  Do you eat the meat you get?
speaker2: Yes I do, and my whole family enjoys. This is why I am so sad that the weather here is not suitable for hunting conditions. Does farming take all your time?

speaker1: It really does.  I mean, you get up before sunrise to work and you work all day past sunset.  You can't take a day off because the crops always need tending to.  That's cool that your whole family likes it!  By the way, have you ever had a deer mounted or stuffed?
speaker2: I have not, my family finds that a little scary! And I never realized how much work you needed to do, is it worth it?
speaker1: I wouldn't know. I just wondered if you had because i've seen it on tv shows and stuff.  Speaking of tv shows, what do you watch with your cat?
speaker2: We don't watch anything specific right now, we just surf through Netflix and sees what appeals to us.
speaker1: Same here.  Have you thought about getting another cat?  I knock the idea around every now and then but haven't yet.
speaker2: I have considered it, but I know it will be a lot of work. This one takes a lot of time as it is.
speaker1: Have you been able to go hunting yet? What is the weather like there?
speaker2: Still a bit cold here, but it is supposed to warm up next week.  I did go out a couple of days ago, but no luck.
speaker1: That's frustrating but I'm sure when the weather picks up you'll get better results! Is it just deer you like to hunt?
speaker2: Yes, just deer.  Although, I would like to hunt elk sometime.  Have you ever considered trying hunting?
speaker1: I've never been hunting before but I think I could try some time. I think working on the farm would have prepared me well for it
response: My thoughts exactly!  Speaking of animals, I wonder if your cat has a 'favorite' show.  My cat loves to watch 'Grimm'. Probably all the creatures, LOL!
entities: My cat sonny was a favorite.
Sonny and I like to watch tv too.
I've never been hunting before but I think I could try some time. I think working on the farm would have prepared me well for it

history: speaker1: Hello, what do you do?
speaker2: I play a lot of video games, specifically league of legends. And you?
speaker1: Cool! I don't often play video games. I like to hunt in my free time.
speaker2: Nice, maybe if you got a new gaming laptop like mine you would play more.
speaker1: What kind of laptop did you get?
speaker2: A new gaming laptop, lol. Wjat do you hunt?
speaker1: Mostly deer. I am worried about overpopulation.
speaker2: Human or deer overpopulation? Do you know who alistar is...a champion!
speaker1: Deer population, I am concerned about wildlife in general. I do not know alistar.
speaker2: Yeah, alistar is my favorite. Good luck with the hunting. You do anything else.
speaker1: Not really, but thank you!
speaker2: Oh well, you should try video games then.
speaker1: I just got back from a trip hunting deer.
speaker2: How did it go?  Did you snag a buck?
speaker1: Not this time.  It still went good though.  I checked out the conditions for some of the animals living in the area.  What have you been up to?

speaker2: I spent all night playing League of Legends.  But after that I bought Resident Evil VIII.  I haven't turned it on yet but I'm looking forward to it.  Usually I wait for a sale but I couldn't resist.
speaker1: That's cool.  What is Resident Evil VIII about?

speaker2: It's a horror game.  You're a guy looking for his kidnapped daughter and you have to explore a bunch of eerie locations full of monsters.  I really liked the last one so I'm eager to see if this one is as good.
speaker1: Hmm, that could be interesting.  Do you play by yourself or is it a multiplayer online game?
speaker2: I just play it by myself.  I turn the lights out and play it late at night by myself so it's as scary as possible.  Do you like horror movies and scary things like that?
speaker1: Not really. About the only thing scary that I like is sneaking up on a deer out in the wild!  I play videogames every now and then but they are usually tame, calm ones.
speaker2: I understand.  Where do you go to hunt?  Is it your land or someone you know?
speaker1: Both actually. Sometimes I hunt on mine or my family's places and sometimes I go to state hunting sites.  You should go next time I go!
speaker2: That would be fun!  I've never shot a real gun before though.  Is it hard?
speaker1: Have you enjoyed the game Resident Evil VIII
speaker2: Yes I have it's a great game! Have you been playing any new games recently?

speaker1: I just don't know if I am brave enough to try Resident Evil yet, but I have been playing a lot of games lately.  I have been playing a lot of Jurassic Park: World lately. So much fun.  Have you played it?
speaker2: No I have not, but that sounds like a ton of fun and something that I would love to play!! Am I able to play it on my gaming laptop?

speaker1: It is pretty graphic intensive, but I think if you have a good gaming laptop it shouldn't be a problem.  I guess it does have some scary moments, but nothing I can't handle. What do you do when you aren't playing games?
speaker2: Most of my free time is spent playing video games, but when I am not playing them I like to play golf to pass the time. Have you ever been golfing?
speaker1: I have been a couple of times, but I think I'm pretty awful.  Where do you usually golf?
speaker2: There is a local golf course that I really enjoy going to
speaker1: Let me know the next time you are going and maybe I can join you?  Maybe the next week I can take you hunting and we can alternate?

speaker2: I don't own my own car! I actually really enjoying walking and running, but then again, I live in a small town and semi-close to work.

speaker2: I'm a computer programmer. What do you do for work.
speaker1: I work in marketing. Do you have any hobbies?
speaker2: I love to grill! I love meat, especially steak.
speaker1: Oh neat! I don't eat meat but I do like some grilled veggies.
speaker2: My family is from alaska. Where are you from?
speaker1: I'm from new england. It must be cold up there.
speaker2: It's so cold! I think thats why I love wearing warm pants!
speaker1: Haha I feel you. I love wearin warm pants in the winter.
speaker2: Do you play any sports?
speaker1: Did you manage to go out on a run today?
speaker2: Yes I actually was able too. I am considering joining the local gym. Do you prefer going to the gym?
speaker1: I do actually.  I like the controlled environment. I don't want to have to depend on the weather consider where I live.
speaker2: Thats why i am thinking about it. I hate to have to run when its raining, and I feel like it rains here all the time.
speaker1: A lot of gyms have tracks so that you can run indoors.  Hey, have you thought about maybe buying a treadmill and using that at home?

speaker2: I am defiantly considering getting one. Im just trying to figure out what i would do more. Go to the gym and actually do more than just running, or sticking to what i know and getting a treadmill.
speaker1: Oh, that's true. I hadn't thought about all of that.  You're right. With a gym there is a whole lot of options for what you can do.  Do you have some good gyms near you?
speaker2: They have just built one in the small town really close to me and it looks pretty decent. Before that it was like an hour drive.
speaker1: With you not owning a car going to any others would probably be difficult.  Well, do you have any good parks and running trails nearby?
speaker2: Yeah exactly. There is a super nice little running trail that is pretty decent.
speaker1: Hey, do you run with anyone?  I mean, have you joined a club or will you if you haven't?
speaker2: There is any around here maybe i could start one. Thank you for that idea.
speaker1: Did you check out that new gym in town?
speaker2: Yeah, I did. I'm not sure I like the vibe there, though.
speaker1: What was wrong with it?
speaker2: The folks there seemed to care more about how they looked than working out. It was a little too trendy for me. I'm pretty plain.
speaker1: Ah, got it. Well, maybe one of the older gyms will work out better for you - or I guess you could get that treadmill you were talking about before. Are you leaning one way or the other yet?
response: I'm leaning towards the treadmill. I think it will work better for my lifestyle. I just don't know which type to get. There are so many choices out there. Do you use a treadmill at your gym? Do you have a suggestion for a home one?

speaker2: Hi how are you tell me about yourself.

speaker2: If you like only mostly eating proteins and no carbohydrates, it works. A crock pot is perfect for cooking up meals

speaker2: I have many keto recipes I can share

speaker2: Hi! Do you like music? I love black sabbath.
speaker1: Dad was in the navy tho so he wouldnt let me listen to black sabbath.
speaker2: That's too bad. Do you work? Workaholic here as I'm in debt.
speaker1: I'm still in school now.
speaker2: I'm 26 and out of school and only think of work all the time.
speaker1: That's too bad. Do you have any pets to cheer you up?
speaker2: No pets. Not my thing, but I love food. What's your favorite?
speaker1: Good old burgers and fries! Yours?
speaker2: I love meat. Call me a carnivore!
speaker1: Haha nice. I like chocolate, too. Named my dogs snickers and bounty.
speaker2: Oh those are such cute names. What kind of dogs?
speaker1: Have you had any days off lately?
speaker2: Not recently, it has been all work and no fun recently. Once I get rid of this debt though, it will all be better.
speaker1: Yeah, I guess once that debt is gone you can have a little extra cash to do some fun stuff.  I'm trying to work my way through school so I can have as little student loan debt as possible.
speaker2: That is a very smart plan. What kind of job do you have right now? I am a grocery store clerk, but I am only doing it until I can find a more permanent job in education.

speaker1: I'm actually driving uber and doing some other gig work.  Surprisingly, it's not a bad way to make some money.  I'm in a bigger city so there's plenty of work that way.  Well I hope you can find a teaching position, we need all the best teachers we can get.  Are you done with school?
speaker2: Yes I am done with school. I am hoping to find some work in the math related field, preferably at a high school. Math is what my major is in.
speaker1: That's good! I thought about being a teacher at one point.  I was kind of a science geek.  Believe it or not I like working with middle school.  They are difficult but still a lot of fun.
speaker2: I understand. Is being a teacher still on the table for you or will you pursue a different career?

speaker1: It's not really on the table anymore.  I like research more than teaching...I like the idea of asking questions other people haven't asked or explored yet.  I'm headed into the social science right now.  Studying people and the way we interact with one another and the environment around us.

speaker2: That is an inspiring and terrific field to enter. And who knows, if teaching doesn't work out, maybe I will find myself in the research field. Hopefully you would be able to give me some pointers.
speaker1: I'd be glad to.  Have you tried any new restaurants recently?
speaker2: I have not really had time to go out recently, so I have just been having fast food recently.

speaker2: I love just about all fast food except McDonald's. It food is so bland! What is your favorite place to get a good burger when you are in a hurry?
speaker1: We have a new place in town called Five Guys. I love it so good. Nice big burgers.

speaker2: We just had one of those open up in my town too! I have been wanting to go there but they don't have a drive thru and I am lazy. Do you have a go to order when you place your order? I know you have to ask for the toppings on your burger.
speaker1: I usually get the double burger with lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, ketchup, mayo and mustard. Plus a small fry I can usually share that with my kids and we all have enough fries.

history: speaker1: Hello, what do you do?
speaker2: I play a lot of video games, specifically league of legends. And you?
speaker1: Cool! I don't often play video games. I like to hunt in my free time.
speaker2: Nice, maybe if you got a new gaming laptop like mine you would play more.
speaker1: What kind of laptop did you get?
speaker2: A new gaming laptop, lol. Wjat do you hunt?
speaker1: Mostly deer. I am worried about overpopulation.
speaker2: Human or deer overpopulation? Do you know who alistar is...a champion!
speaker1: Deer population, I am concerned about wildlife in general. I do not know alistar.
speaker2: Yeah, alistar is my favorite. Good luck with the hunting. You do anything else.
speaker1: Not really, but thank you!
speaker2: Oh well, you should try video games then.
speaker1: I just got back from a trip hunting deer.
speaker2: How did it go?  Did you snag a buck?
speaker1: Not this time.  It still went good though.  I checked out the conditions for some of the animals living in the area.  What have you been up to?

speaker2: I spent all night playing League of Legends.  But after that I bought Resident Evil VIII.  I haven't turned it on yet but I'm looking forward to it.  Usually I wait for a sale but I couldn't resist.
speaker1: That's cool.  What is Resident Evil VIII about?

speaker2: It's a horror game.  You're a guy looking for his kidnapped daughter and you have to explore a bunch of eerie locations full of monsters.  I really liked the last one so I'm eager to see if this one is as good.
speaker1: Hmm, that could be interesting.  Do you play by yourself or is it a multiplayer online game?
speaker2: I just play it by myself.  I turn the lights out and play it late at night by myself so it's as scary as possible.  Do you like horror movies and scary things like that?
speaker1: Not really. About the only thing scary that I like is sneaking up on a deer out in the wild!  I play videogames every now and then but they are usually tame, calm ones.
speaker2: I understand.  Where do you go to hunt?  Is it your land or someone you know?
speaker1: Both actually. Sometimes I hunt on mine or my family's places and sometimes I go to state hunting sites.  You should go next time I go!
speaker2: That would be fun!  I've never shot a real gun before though.  Is it hard?
speaker1: Have you enjoyed the game Resident Evil VIII
speaker2: Yes I have it's a great game! Have you been playing any new games recently?

speaker1: I just don't know if I am brave enough to try Resident Evil yet, but I have been playing a lot of games lately.  I have been playing a lot of Jurassic Park: World lately. So much fun.  Have you played it?
speaker2: No I have not, but that sounds like a ton of fun and something that I would love to play!! Am I able to play it on my gaming laptop?

speaker1: It is pretty graphic intensive, but I think if you have a good gaming laptop it shouldn't be a problem.  I guess it does have some scary moments, but nothing I can't handle. What do you do when you aren't playing games?
response: Most of my free time is spent playing video games, but when I am not playing them I like to play golf to pass the time. Have you ever been golfing?
entities: What do you do when you aren't playing games?

history: speaker1: Hello, how are you today?
speaker2: Great and you?
speaker1: Good, just finished eating some chocolate ice cream.
speaker2: Chocolate ice cream, yumm that's about the same color as my hair ;-).
speaker1: My dad had brown hair too; he was in the military.
speaker2: I love my family, my mother works with special needs clients.
speaker1: That's awesome! I just read a book about autism; I love to read.
speaker2: Me too! But I had no choice growing up latina, mom always pushed education.
speaker1: Same for me. Maybe that's why I work for a small nonprofit that helps underprivileged youths.
speaker2: Lol I kind of went the other route and became a healer.
speaker1: That's awesome. Well, it was nice talking with you today!
speaker2: It really was fun, thanks!
speaker1: I was at the book store and found a great new book to read on the advantages of working with youth in the community.
speaker2: Oh wow that sounds awesome, what are some of the tips they give?
speaker1: I haven't started it yet, so I am not sure, but I will fill you in once I read it! How was your day today, what exactly do you do as a healer?
speaker2: Basically it is a therapy type thing. I listen to people vent about their problems and give them advice that helps them clear their mind.
speaker1: That sounds interesting. Where did you go to do your training to become a healer?
speaker2: I got my degree in mindfulness at the local community college, I then trained under a healer at a local therapy location
speaker1: Oh that's great! What do you like to do when you are not healing people?
speaker2: I really enjoy reading, a big fan of biography books
speaker1: I love to read too, but I am more interested in fiction. What is the best biography you have read?
speaker2: The best auto-biography I ever read was about the life of Martin Luther King Jr. Super inspiring. What is your favorite fiction book?
speaker1: I bet that book was extremely inspiring! I love murder mysteries right now, but my all time favorite book would have to be To Kill a Mockingbird.
speaker2: To Kill a Mockingbird is an absolutely legendary book, something everyone needs to read.
speaker1: Was it difficult to earn your degree in mindfulness?
speaker2: It was not difficult. I learned some of it from a local healer so it was easy for me in school.
speaker1: Wow thats awesome. What was it working under a healer ?
speaker2: It was a great experience working under a healer. He thought me the nuisances of healing.that you cannot learn from books

speaker2: I got my degree in mindfulness at the local community college, I then trained under a healer at a local therapy location
speaker1: Oh that's great! What do you like to do when you are not healing people?
speaker2: I really enjoy reading, a big fan of biography books
speaker1: I love to read too, but I am more interested in fiction. What is the best biography you have read?
speaker2: The best auto-biography I ever read was about the life of Martin Luther King Jr. Super inspiring. What is your favorite fiction book?
speaker1: I bet that book was extremely inspiring! I love murder mysteries right now, but my all time favorite book would have to be To Kill a Mockingbird.
speaker2: To Kill a Mockingbird is an absolutely legendary book, something everyone needs to read.
speaker1: Was it difficult to earn your degree in mindfulness?
speaker2: It was not difficult. I learned some of it from a local healer so it was easy for me in school.
speaker1: Wow thats awesome. What was it working under a healer ?
speaker2: It was a great experience working under a healer. He thought me the nuisances of healing.that you cannot learn from books
speaker1: Its always good to have first hand experience. I have just finished reading a new mystery book.
speaker2: oh really, what book was that?
speaker1: gone girl there was a movie based on it, eating icecream while reading a book is such a comfortable feeling. Try reading it if you have free time
speaker2: The name 'gone girl' is familiar. I am going to look it up after work.
speaker1: Yes it was a best selling book at one point. You said your favorite book is biography of Martin luther king why?
speaker2: I like how united the country and people together for a cause
speaker1: Yes he was such an inspiration to the black community wish we have such a leader today
speaker2: yes I agree. It is not like the days set in the book 'To Kill a Mockingbird' but there is still inequality.
speaker1: I just started reading another murder mystery, The Last Goodbye. I can't put it down.
speaker2: What's it about? I've started the new Michelle Obama autobiography a couple of days ago.

speaker1: Well I don't want to spoil too much of its content since it's a murder mystery, but basically a woman who can talk to spirits connect people with their deceased loved ones. And how was your reading of Michelle Obama's autobiography?

speaker2: I've never been really involved in politics, so it was interesting to read about the initiatives she's started during her time as first lady. Your book sounds very interesting, has a mix of paranormal storytelling in there too.
speaker1: Yeah I definitely recommend you to read it if you get a chance! Speaking of which do you have any other book recommendations?
speaker2: Hmm.... let me think about it.... Is there a certain topic you enjoy and want to learn more about, like crime, science, etc? It'll give me an idea of what book to recommend.
speaker1: I usually prefer murder mysteries but I do want to expand my genera, I think some non fiction books like with science or food might be interesting.

speaker2: You know what? I bet you'd love Mindhunter. Have you heard of it? They even made it into a Netflix show. It's about these two FBI agents that start the department for serial killers, and the stories of their interviews with famous ones.
speaker1: Oh I never did, the premise sounds interesting so I might take a look! Do you think the book is better or the show is better?
speaker2: The show does a great job of making the stories feel real, but I always think the books are better. There's just so many details that get cut out that make it a more enjoyable read.
speaker1: I guess that's the case with basically all the adoptions I can think of haha, the book will always have more details. Oh also I'm thinking of joining a book club lately!
response: Does it meet online, or in person? I think the in-person ones sound really interesting, I just can never find the time with my job. I'm usually busy from early morning all the way into the evening.
entities: I'm thinking of joining a book club lately!

history: speaker1: Hi.
speaker2: Hello, I am about to take a lunch break and eat french fries.
speaker1: I just finished my lunch I had a burger from chikfella and a chocolate milkshake.
speaker2: Yum, what do you do for work? I am on work trip right now.
speaker1: I work for jnj. Anything planned for the weeked?
speaker2: Cool, yes I am going fishing how about you?
speaker1: I am going snowboarding should be fun.
speaker2: Wow, I have never been snowboarding before.
speaker1: Try it sometime. What kind of car do you drive?
speaker2: I don't live close to any mountians, I drive a suv because I have a family.
speaker1: I am buying a new car, any recommendations?
speaker2: Honda's are very reliable.
speaker1: Yes honda is good I have a good deal on a nissan altima 2012 for 6k.
speaker2: Wow that is a good deal! I would take that.
speaker1: I bought that Nissan, it feels nice to have a clean car that works again!
speaker2: That's great! Is it a new car? f you don't mind me asking, how much did you spend?
speaker1: It is. It was a steal for 20,000. What did you spend on your Suv?
speaker2: Oh, man, I almost don't wanna tell you... 48K. It's huge! I love to camp and fish for a week at a time, so it's the right size for me....
speaker1: Wow! What kind is it? Have you camped with it before?

speaker2: I bought it a couple of years back, and I take it out two or three times a year, depending upon how much time I can take off work. I camp in a big tent for the family, but the SUV is roomy enough we can stay in there if we want....
speaker1: That makes sense. Do you have a different car that you drive more regularly? I'm not a huge camper myself.

speaker2: I see I didn't tell you what it is: a Ford Expedition. I have a Toyota Corolla for in-city driving. For me and the family, we *have* to get out in nature at least twice a year. I just wish we lived closer to mountains, because there's nothing like trout fishing in mountain streams!
speaker1: I lived near the mountains but never got used to driving in them. I need lessons for that. I always made my friends drive on snowboarding trips.
speaker2: I got over my fear of driving in the mountains after doing Going-to-the-Sun Road in Glacier several times in the late-'90s. I wish I knew how to snowboard.
speaker1: It definitely can be harder to learn as an adult. Do you ski instead?
speaker2: No, just camp, fish, and hike in the hills, no real mountains. Sometimes we take the bikes and ride the foot paths.
speaker1: Do your kids and wife enjoy camping and the outdoors as much as you?
speaker2: They are usually good for one trip a year and the other two times I go with some camping buddies.  My family are pretty good campers, but one weekend is usually enough.
speaker1: And it is nice to get out with friends too. Do you usually visit the same spots?

speaker2: With my family there are usually a couple places that aren't too far from 'civilization' (as my wife calls it).  With my friends, it's whatever interests us.  We try to alternate who picks and we like to keep it within a three hour range from home if possible.
speaker1: That's great! Do you do the whole s'mores and ghost stories thing with the kids or is it more fishing and hiking?
response: With the kids we do lots of smores, but no ghost stories.  As for my friends, it's fishing/hiking until almost sundown!  We are usually too beat to do much more than clean the fish, cook, and eat!  Do you think you would ever be up for that?
entities: just camp, fish, and hike in the hills, no real mountains.

history: speaker1: Hello have you ever seen the show extreme couponing it’s my favorite.
speaker2: Yes I love that show really helps when you have lots of different food to buy.
speaker1: My coupon habit has let me buy food for all my animals and paint supplies.
speaker2: I love to read lots of books.
speaker1: Going to college full time sometimes makes it hard to get into a good book.
speaker2: That's true. What are your hobbies or other interests?
speaker1: Besides taking sunset walks I enjoy spending time with my 5 dogs and 3 rats.
speaker2: Sounds very interesting. I enjoy riding my bike.
speaker1: I could paint you riding your bike.
speaker2: That would be nice. Do you listen to music while painting?
speaker1: No I do not.
speaker2: Since your a student, if you need your computer fixed, I'm your guy.
speaker1: What books have you been recently recently then?
speaker2: I have been reading some classics, like To Kill a Mockingbird and The Great Gatsby. Have you read those?
speaker1: Yes! 3 of my dogs' names are Scout, Daisy, and Gatsby! Those are my absolute favorites.
speaker2: Wow that is amazing. They are some really well-written books. Have you seen the movies accompanying those books?
speaker1: I have. I liked both of the versions of The Great Gatsby. Did you like either the older or newer one better if you've seen them?
speaker2: I have seen both, but I have to go with the newer one. I think Leonardo Dicaprio is a terrific actor.
speaker1: I do too! I can't believe it took so long for him to get an Oscar. He chooses very good diverse roles. Is he your favorite actor?
speaker2: He is one of them, along with John Krasinski who is most famous for his role in The Office.
speaker1: I love The Office! It got me through finals, and John Krasinski is wonderful. I like his Good News Network stuff.
speaker2: I'll have to check that out! Is it a relief to have finally gotten through finals, I'm sure you have been busy?
speaker1: With 8 pets, I'm always busy. Do you have any pets?
speaker2: I have two dogs. They are a handful, but I am able to cuddle up with them and read a good book which is always fun!
speaker1: I stopped by a book store that recently opened on my way home from classes. One of the guys working there looks a lot like John Krasinski!
speaker2: I also see him everywhere ! It must be because we often think about him. How was he dressed ?
speaker1: He was dressed in his normal attire. He had on a backwards hat, khakias and a polo.
speaker2: That is a weird outfit for someone who works in a bookstore, maybe it was the real John Krasinski doing some research for a new role .
speaker1: Honestly, thats what I'm thinking. He just kept walking around looking at everything and he even had a small notepad that he was taking notes on.
speaker2: That does not sounds like a real employee, maybe a reporter. Did he talk to someone ?
speaker1: No but he noticed me following him around and did one of those awkward head nods. Whats your favorite movie with him in it?
speaker2: I really like the Office, but it is not a movie. I did not like much his movies, besides A Quiet Place.
speaker1: The office is the greatest show ever written. I've watched the entire series 3 complete times.
speaker2: I always watch one episode when I do my exercises. Sometimes, it is dangerous because I laugh so much !
speaker1: Yes! I would love a spin off show with John Krasinski and just Michael Scott.

history: speaker1: Hi, tracy here. I love people and fast cars. You sing?
speaker2: Hi tracy. Amanda here. I enjoy going to the gym alongside my vegan diet.
speaker1: I see. I love being helpful and I paint art. Are you an artist?
speaker2: I don't sing, but love art. My lawyer husband is an artist as well.
speaker1: Get out! I am a paralegal. I love helping people too. You bake?
speaker2: Whoa! Funny you say that, my jeep is loaded with baked goods right now!
speaker1: Great! I would love to paint that picture. You dance?
speaker2: If you call zumba dancing! Lol! What is your favorite vacations spot?
speaker1: Niagra falls. It is an artist paradise. You like to travel?
speaker2: I love traveling, especially to the mountains. They are a good workout!
speaker1: Me too! I like fast cars and new people. Nice to meet you.
speaker2: You as well. I love vehicles that can tackle rough terrain, like my jeep wrangler.
speaker1: What kind of things do you bake as a vegan?
speaker2: My favorite has to be a version of a vegan pizza.  That is the food I miss the most!! Are you vegan too?

speaker1: No, but my best friend is trying to become one. She is a vegetarian, but being a vegan can be so hard when you love cheese. Lol I always make a delicious roasted veggie dish to bring to her house for parties. Do you find cutting out cheese a challenge too?

speaker2: Very much so, all dairy in general! But it does get easier after you figure out what good substitutes you can enjoy.  I feel lucky that there are so many choices out there now.  Do you have any trips coming up this summer?
speaker1: I hope to travel to the smokey mountains soon. It is one of my favorite places on Earth. Have you ever been there? It's so peaceful and being up so high just surrounded by trees is magical!

speaker2: I went there when I was very young actually! My only memories are of dollywood and the long, winding roads!! I'm sure now going as an adult I would have a much more rich experience.  That would be a great place to bring the Jeep now that I think of it!

speaker1: Oh yeah. The last time I visited we rented a 4 wheel drive and it was worth it. We were climbing the mountains to reach our chalet. speaker1: No, but my best friend is trying to become one. She is a vegetarian, but being a vegan can be so hard when you love cheese. Lol I always make a delicious roasted veggie dish to bring to her house for parties. Do you find cutting out cheese a challenge too?

speaker2: Very much so, all dairy in general! But it does get easier after you figure out what good substitutes you can enjoy.  I feel lucky that there are so many choices out there now.  Do you have any trips coming up this summer?
speaker1: I hope to travel to the smokey mountains soon. It is one of my favorite places on Earth. Have you ever been there? It's so peaceful and being up so high just surrounded by trees is magical!

speaker2: I went there when I was very young actually! My only memories are of dollywood and the long, winding roads!! I'm sure now going as an adult I would have a much more rich experience.  That would be a great place to bring the Jeep now that I think of it!

speaker1: Oh yeah. The last time I visited we rented a 4 wheel drive and it was worth it. We were climbing the mountains to reach our chalet. It was so wild heading up the side of a mountain, looking over the side. Yikes! When I was there we didn't head to Dollywood, but we were close to it. Where in the mountains do you hike when you do?

speaker2: That sounds like a perfect time for you.  When I'm hiking, the steeper the mountain, the better!! I like to take day trips where I know I'll be out for about 8 hours or so.  They are very tough to do, but if you're prepared it becomes a very rewarding experience!!
speaker1: Wow. That sounds like an amazing day trip for sure. I'm not sure I have the stamina for such an intense hiking experience. Have you ever ran into any trouble while hiking?

speaker2: There was one time where I got lost as it was starting to get dark out...I bring my tent and supplies to sleep overnight so I was prepared to sleep out there if I had to but luckily I ran into a couple just about when I was ready to give up!! I don't know how I'd handle seeing a bear or something like that out by myself.

speaker1: I'm so glad you didn't cross paths with anything scary like that! I don't know what I'd do if a bear crossed my path either. I've been pretty lucky to never have one near our cabin in the Mountains either. They always warn us about them though, so we are prepared. Do you have a pretty big tent you use? Or an individual one?

speaker2: Its just an individual tent that is VERY small.  I just bring a backpack so everything has to be as small as possible. Luckily I have not had to use it yet!!  Do you paint when you're in the mountains too?
speaker1: My friend told me she's having another house party. Do you have any ideas for vegan dishes I could bring?

speaker2: Depending on what kind of party it is, if it's a buffet then there are some great vegan sausage rolls in the supermarkets now, and also vegan pizzas and burgers. If it's a bit more of a sit down dinner, vegan curries are so easy to make. I made one last week with sweet potatoes, red pepper, chickpeas, onion and garlic. It can be served with rice or other grains.
speaker1: That sounds amazing. I am just starting on this vegan journey. Do you have any suggestions for cook books?

speaker2: There's a book called 'The Plant Kitchen' which is quite good but I can't remember where I got it. You can borrow it if you like! I was also going to say to you that there's a cheese shop nearby that has started doing loads of vegan cheeses... here come the cheese and wine nights!

speaker1: Really? I would love to borrow it. I've spent time at the market looking around and even the farmers market. It just seems so overhwelming at the moment but I know the long term benefits far outweigh my confusing right now.

speaker2: When I first went vegetarian (before I thought about going vegan), I realised the best way to do it was eat what you would normally, but just miss out the meat. For example, if you're getting Chinese food, have whatever you usually have (my fave is sweet and sour), but just get the veggie version. Gradually I realised that I wasn't missing the meat at all as I was still eating my favourite dishes. What's your favorite food?
speaker1: So like with Chinese food I can still order my favorite...beef and brocoli but without the meat. What about tofu? Do you eat that?

speaker2: Haha yes in that case you might need to find a replacement for the beef. Tofu would be a good substitute but it's got a very different texture. I do eat tofu sometimes, I chop up a block of it into cubes and oven bake it, or I marinade it in BBQ flavourings and fry it on the pan. It's great with all sorts of things.
speaker1: Is it like rubbery? I can't do rubber feeling things. I think I would have to be like you and just cover it in sauce. How do you get your protein?

speaker2: Tofu can be rubbery if you don't make it crispy. But if it's fried properly it's so delicious; crisp on the outside and softer on the inside. I get protein from peanut butter, brown rice, quinoa, beans, oats for breakfast and loads of veggies. I've always loved vegetables though, so it was quite easy for me to convert! What's your favorite vegetable?

speaker1: You know, I never even thought about frying it. I'm heading to Trader Joes later today so hopefully I will be able to have more choices. I never thought of vegetables as a protein source. I love all veggies.

speaker2: Things like broccoli, kale, spinach and even sweetcorn are good protein sources. Also if you work out a lot you can get protein shakes with vegan protein added to them, but I've never tried that before!
speaker1: I just tried the best recipe for vegan beef and broccoli!
speaker2: What did you think! I'm always curious about what non-vegans think about vegan recipes. When I was a meat-eater, I was surprised how good they were!
speaker1: I am enjoying the food but it will take some time for my insides to get used to all the veg!
response: Haha, that makes sense. Don't worry, I always manage to make my friends understand why I love veggies so much. Me, you, and your vegetarian friend can meet up every week and learn a new recipe if you're down!
entities: No, but my best friend is trying to become one.
I am enjoying the food but it will take some time for my insides to get used to all the veg!

speaker1: Get out! I am a paralegal. I love helping people too. You bake?
speaker2: Whoa! Funny you say that, my jeep is loaded with baked goods right now!
speaker1: Great! I would love to paint that picture. You dance?
speaker2: If you call zumba dancing! Lol! What is your favorite vacations spot?
speaker1: Niagra falls. It is an artist paradise. You like to travel?
speaker2: I love traveling, especially to the mountains. They are a good workout!
speaker1: Me too! I like fast cars and new people. Nice to meet you.
speaker2: You as well. I love vehicles that can tackle rough terrain, like my jeep wrangler.
speaker1: What kind of things do you bake as a vegan?
speaker2: My favorite has to be a version of a vegan pizza.  That is the food I miss the most!! Are you vegan too?

speaker1: No, but my best friend is trying to become one. She is a vegetarian, but being a vegan can be so hard when you love cheese. Lol I always make a delicious roasted veggie dish to bring to her house for parties. Do you find cutting out cheese a challenge too?

speaker2: Very much so, all dairy in general! But it does get easier after you figure out what good substitutes you can enjoy.  I feel lucky that there are so many choices out there now.  Do you have any trips coming up this summer?
speaker1: I hope to travel to the smokey mountains soon. It is one of my favorite places on Earth. Have you ever been there? It's so peaceful and being up so high just surrounded by trees is magical!

speaker2: I went there when I was very young actually! My only memories are of dollywood and the long, winding roads!! I'm sure now going as an adult I would have a much more rich experience.  That would be a great place to bring the Jeep now that I think of it!

speaker1: Oh yeah. The last time I visited we rented a 4 wheel drive and it was worth it. We were climbing the mountains to reach our chalet. It was so wild heading up the side of a mountain, looking over the side. Yikes! When I was there we didn't head to Dollywood, but we were close to it. Where in the mountains do you hike when you do?

speaker2: That sounds like a perfect time for you.  When I'm hiking, the steeper the mountain, the better!! I like to take day trips where I know I'll be out for about 8 hours or so.  They are very tough to do, but if you're prepared it becomes a very rewarding experience!!
speaker1: Wow. That sounds like an amazing day trip for sure. I'm not sure I have the stamina for such an intense hiking experience. Have you ever ran into any trouble while hiking?

speaker2: There was one time where I got lost as it was starting to get dark out...I bring my tent and supplies to sleep overnight so I was prepared to sleep out there if I had to but luckily I ran into a couple just about when I was ready to give up!! I don't know how I'd handle seeing a bear or something like that out by myself.

speaker1: I'm so glad you didn't cross paths with anything scary like that! I don't know what I'd do if a bear crossed my path either. I've been pretty lucky to never have one near our cabin in the Mountains either. They always warn us about them though, so we are prepared. Do you have a pretty big tent you use? Or an individual one?

speaker2: Its just an individual tent that is VERY small.  I just bring a backpack so everything has to be as small as possible. Luckily I have not had to use it yet!!  Do you paint when you're in the mountains too?
speaker1: My friend told me she's having another house party. Do you have any ideas for vegan dishes I could bring?

speaker2: Depending on what kind of party it is, if it's a buffet then there are some great vegan sausage rolls in the supermarkets now, and also vegan pizzas and burgers. If it's a bit more of a sit down dinner, vegan curries are so easy to make. I made one last week with sweet potatoes, red pepper, chickpeas, onion and garlic. It can be served with rice or other grains.
speaker1: That sounds amazing. I am just starting on this vegan journey. Do you have any suggestions for cook books?

speaker2: There's a book called 'The Plant Kitchen' which is quite good but I can't remember where I got it. You can borrow it if you like! I was also going to say to you that there's a cheese shop nearby that has started doing loads of vegan cheeses... here come the cheese and wine nights!

speaker1: Really? I would love to borrow it. I've spent time at the market looking around and even the farmers market. It just seems so overhwelming at the moment but I know the long term benefits far outweigh my confusing right now.

speaker2: When I first went vegetarian (before I thought about going vegan), I realised the best way to do it was eat what you would normally, but just miss out the meat. For example, if you're getting Chinese food, have whatever you usually have (my fave is sweet and sour), but just get the veggie version. Gradually I realised that I wasn't missing the meat at all as I was still eating my favourite dishes. What's your favorite food?
speaker1: So like with Chinese food I can still order my favorite...beef and brocoli but without the meat. What about tofu? Do you eat that?

speaker2: Haha yes in that case you might need to find a replacement for the beef. Tofu would be a good substitute but it's got a very different texture. I do eat tofu sometimes, I chop up a block of it into cubes and oven bake it, or I marinade it in BBQ flavourings and fry it on the pan. It's great with all sorts of things.
speaker1: Is it like rubbery? I can't do rubber feeling things. I think I would have to be like you and just cover it in sauce. How do you get your protein?

speaker2: Tofu can be rubbery if you don't make it crispy. But if it's fried properly it's so delicious; crisp on the outside and softer on the inside. I get protein from peanut butter, brown rice, quinoa, beans, oats for breakfast and loads of veggies. I've always loved vegetables though, so it was quite easy for me to convert! What's your favorite vegetable?

speaker1: You know, I never even thought about frying it. I'm heading to Trader Joes later today so hopefully I will be able to have more choices. I never thought of vegetables as a protein source. I love all veggies.

speaker2: Things like broccoli, kale, spinach and even sweetcorn are good protein sources. Also if you work out a lot you can get protein shakes with vegan protein added to them, but I've never tried that before!
speaker1: I just tried the best recipe for vegan beef and broccoli!
speaker2: What did you think! I'm always curious about what non-vegans think about vegan recipes. When I was a meat-eater, I was surprised how good they were!
speaker1: I am enjoying the food but it will take some time for my insides to get used to all the veg!

speaker2: Haha, that makes sense. Don't worry, I always manage to make my friends understand why I love veggies so much. Me, you, and your vegetarian friend can meet up every week and learn a new recipe if you're down!
speaker1: That would be awesome, we should definitely share recipes. What is your favorite meal using tofu?

speaker2: I recently tried a Korean tofu recipe and i LOVED it! It used gochujang, a spicy paste that a lot of Korean recipes use. I love spicy food, it makes everythng so delicious. Do you like spicy stuff?
speaker1: Wow, I never thought about making a spicy meal with tofu. Thanks for the idea! How did you find your performance at the gym after going fully vegan?

speaker2: Its interesting, I actually had a lot more energy once I went vegan! That's how I can do my eight hour hikes. I feel like a lot of athletic guys think that meat is necessary to get buff in the gym. It's actually a myth that vegetarian food doesn't have enough protein.
speaker1: Interesting, I do not think I could do a 8 hour hike but going vegan might help then.
speaker2: Honestly, even just doing zumba classes gives me the same endorphins that I get from my hikes. Next time I go to a zumba class, you should come!
speaker1: I have never done Zumba but it does sound fun. I need to wait for my body to get used to just veggies first, do not want to be constantly passing gas while doing Zumba.
response: Lol, you'd be surprised how quickly it can happen. Plus, vegan food isn't just all vegges. There's tofu, seitan, beans, rice, quinoa, pasta... the list goes on! You can actually eat a pretty unhealthy diet while being vegan with no veggies if you wanted.
entities: I need to wait for my body to get used to just veggies first, do not want to be constantly passing gas while doing Zumba.

history: speaker1: Hello, I just got done working out at the gym. What are you doing?
speaker2: Getting ready to take my dogs bounty and snickers to the park for a run.
speaker1: Cute! I wish I owned dogs. That sounds like fun.
speaker2: I love dogs. Being an only child they were my family growing up.
speaker1: Awe, my husband and I work to much and can't have pets.
speaker2: I understand. Where did you go to school?.
speaker1: I went to school in texas, for nutrition..
speaker2: I studied art history in france and spain.
speaker1: Cool, that was probably a great experience.
speaker2: Yeah, I was a navy brat so I got to travel quite a bit..
speaker1: Cool, where else have you lived?
speaker2: Kuwait, hawaii, california, and florida.
speaker1: I like to travel too, but only where my jeep wrangler will take me.
speaker2: I'd love a jeep. Right now I use mass transit to get around.
speaker1: How did living in Kuwait compare to living in the more 'western' areas?
speaker2: The biggest difference would be having to learn a new language. However, I was able to adjust. Have you ever learned a new language?

speaker1: I learned a lot of Spanish, believe it or not, when I lived in Texas! Since its so close to the border you easily can pick up on it.  Although I do want to go to Italy this summer and thought it would be fun to learn a little before I do that.  Do you have any vacations coming up?
speaker2: Yes, I am planning a trip to Japan in the summer. With all my traveling, it's surprising that I have never been to Asia before!
speaker1: Wow well that sounds like a bucket list trip! Will you be visiting any art museums while you're there?
speaker2: Yes, I have a few planned that I am going to see. When you travel, do you visit art museums?
speaker1: Not typically! I tend to stick to outdoor adventures.  Last time I visited Mexico we went offroading on 4 wheelers, that is more what I love to do! How are your dogs doing?
speaker2: They are doing great, and I can tell they are looking forward to a good vacation. Will you be getting a dog soon or do you not have the time?

speaker1: I didn't know your dogs traveled with you, how cool!  Between traveling and work, we decided not to get a dog.  We are looking into getting a cat though, they seem a little bit easier to take care of! Sounds like they don't want you around most of the day anyhow, haha! Have you ever had a cat?
speaker2: I have actually not had a cat. I feel like they would not get along well with my dogs, so I'll probably just stay a dog person.
speaker1: I feel like I don't meet many cat people! They definitely are not as friendly as dogs are, that's for sure. That sounds like a good idea, don't mess up a good thing!
speaker2: That is the goal! But I do know that cats are very lovable, and I'm sure it will be perfect for you!
speaker1: My coworker happens to know someone with kittens. I might go meet them.
speaker2: That sounds like a wonderful idea. I had a friend at school whose parents fostered kittens, and they were so cute to visit although I don't think I could handle so many myself.
speaker1: Do you really think so?
speaker2: They had about fifteen of them at once! And the kittens need a little more care when they're young. Maybe one day I'd foster a dog.
speaker1: Woah That is a lot of kittens!
response: Yes! Does your coworker enjoy having kittens?
entities: My coworker happens to know someone with kittens. I might go meet them.

history: speaker1: Hello, I just finished my daily run outside.
speaker2: Cool, do you compete running or just stay fit.
speaker1: Just do it exercise and leisure! What do you do?
speaker2: I play video games, mostly with friends.
speaker1: Cool, I have never played video games but I would to try.
speaker2: League of legends is my favorite and alistar is my favorite champion.
speaker1: I have heard of league of legends my friends play that.
speaker2: Last month I bought a new gaming laptop which is really cool.
speaker1: Wow, I don't enjoy computer games that much. I like to be outside.
speaker2: I understand, do you do exercise other than running.
speaker1: I like to swim too, I also enjoy walking my dog..
speaker2: Swimming is good for you too.
speaker1: How has the new gaming laptop been working for you when you play League of Legends?
speaker2: It's been great. Works really well, great visuals. I know you're not a gamer, but I'd highly recommend the brand if you were ever in the market for a computer.
speaker1: You are right, but all my friends like to play! I just got through with my first marathon. It was a real challenge.
speaker2: Oh gosh I can only imagine! How did you feel at the end of it?
speaker1: I was drained and dehydrated. I always run at a faster pace when I'm in a crowd of people and it really got to me.
speaker2: I have to admit, I've never been much of a runner unless I'm being chased, lol! I do enjoy swimming, though.
speaker1: That's another one of favorite activities. I'm a better runner than a swimmer however.
speaker2: Swimming feels so good on my knees. They get so sore. Have you ever tried getting your dog to swim with you?
speaker1: Yes! I go some in the lake and my dog loves it. I guess it is true. Dogs are man's best friend.
speaker2: Haha, my poor dog is so ridiculous. She's terrified of a bath, but she loves to jump into a muddy lake.
speaker1: I need to take a run or swim tomorrow before I get too lazy!!!
speaker2: Now that it's getting warmer swimming will feel really good.
speaker1: My dog and I are checking out a new lake this weekend. Hopefully it isn't too muddy.
speaker2: Sound fantastic, what kind of dog do you have?
speaker1: I have a Sheltie, a Shetland Sheepdog. His name is Buddy. How about you? What kind of dog do you have?
speaker2: A Labrador Retriever which explains jumping in a muddy lake. I bet it takes forever to dry Buddy out after a swim.

speaker1: It sure does. Luckily, he doesn't like to go swimming. He mostly stands in the shallow water and barks while I swim. Labs love the water don't they? Funny that yours doesn't like the bath, though.
speaker2: The only thing I can imagine is that bath water is too clean for her. Shelties are really big, aren't they? What do you drive him around in?

speaker1: Yeah, and maybe the enclosed space is a little freaky for her. Shelties are mid-sized. They are like little Lassie dogs. Buddy is about 25 pounds, so he fits in the backseat of my car just fine. I own a Honda Accord, so Buddy just hangs in the backseat.
speaker2: Oh, that's a great size for a dog. I bet he's the best running companion, can he run a whole marathon with you?

speaker1: Shelties are more of a sprinter type dog. Not made for long distance. They were bred to herd sheep, so lots of starts and stops. I don't take Buddy with me when I run, as he slows me down! Ha! Does your dog swim with you?
speaker2: I guess you could say we start swimming together, but she quickly out paces me and if there is any waterfowl, she's just gone.

speaker1: I can just picture that! Buddy is the same with cats. When he sees one, he's off. Luckily, he's pretty obedient, so he doesn't go far. He's a working dog, so he's happiest when he has a 'job'.
response: What sort of jobs have you invented for him? Retrievers, you know, just bring things back so there is no imagination needed.
entities: He's a working dog, so he's happiest when he has a 'job'.

speaker2: Oh gosh I can only imagine! How did you feel at the end of it?

speaker1: My dog and I are checking out a new lake this weekend. Hopefully it isn't too muddy.

speaker1: Shelties are more of a sprinter type dog. Not made for long distance. They were bred to herd sheep, so lots of starts and stops. I don't take Buddy with me when I run, as he slows me down! Ha! Does your dog swim with you?

history: speaker1: Just got up and ready for the day. How are you today?
speaker2: Pretty good. You?.
speaker1: Not bad. Trying to get motivated.
speaker2: I know how feel. Coffee lots of coffee.
speaker1: Sometimes it still seems like it's not enough.
speaker2: True there. But I am an entrepreneur so it is easier for me I guess.
speaker1: That's awesome. Nothing extraordinary over here. Except maybe my hair, with it being bright red.
speaker2: Lucky you!! Mine is just a plain brown.
speaker1: Sometimes wish it was plain, lots of questions asking if it's natural.
speaker2: True. People are mean sometimes. What do you like to do?
speaker1: Biking and hiking are two favorites. How about you?
speaker2: I like going to the ocean with my dog (a.k.a. My best friend) :).
speaker1: What kind of dog is it that you have?
speaker2: She's a cocker spaniel named Susie. She's fantastic and I love her.
speaker1: Aww she sounds so sweet! How old is she?
speaker2: About five years old. She's very friendly and smart. When it's time for walks, she gets her leash and brings it over. haha
speaker1: That's adorable! What part of the country are you in? Is it easy to walk her year-round?
speaker2: I live in the northeast, but I travel a lot. She's not a fan of the cold, but when I can travel to warmer areas, she comes with me. Do you have any pets?
speaker1: I've been thinking about getting a dog, but I have so much trouble making up my mind on what kind to get! What suggestions do you have?

speaker2: Well, it depends a lot on what you have in mind. When looking for a pet, think about things like: Will you have time to take care of them? If you have to travel, can they come with or do you have someone to look in on them? Do you want a quiet pet? Do you want a pet to play with? etc., etc. There's a lot to think about. I got my girl because she's easy to travel with and very friendly.
speaker1: I should probably think about getting a smaller breed, in all honesty. Have you ever owned a large dog?

speaker2: I have. My family had a golden retriever when I was young. He was a great dog. He's play with us out in the yard and go with us on walks around the block. He didn't like to be cooped up indoors, though. It's a good things we were very active kids. haha
speaker1: So what exactly do you do as an entrepreneur? What line of business are you in?
speaker2: I am in the dropshipping business, if you know what that entails?
speaker1: Hmm I'm not quite sure what is. Could you elaborate?

speaker2: So, I essentially act as a middle man between suppliers and distributers. I list products from them to a large audience, on a platform, and mark up the price because of my exposure to potential clients.
speaker1: Oh that makes sense! Do you enjoy your work? Does it require a lot of traveling?
response: No, it is all remote, I never see the products, I just act as an advertiser really. It is very easy for the money it generates. Do you travel a lot?
entities: Do you enjoy your work? Does it require a lot of traveling?
I essentially act as a middle man between suppliers and distributers. I list products from them to a large audience, on a platform, and mark up the price because of my exposure to potential clients.

history: speaker1: Just got up and ready for the day. How are you today?
speaker2: Pretty good. You?.
speaker1: Not bad. Trying to get motivated.
speaker2: I know how feel. Coffee lots of coffee.
speaker1: Sometimes it still seems like it's not enough.
speaker2: True there. But I am an entrepreneur so it is easier for me I guess.
speaker1: That's awesome. Nothing extraordinary over here. Except maybe my hair, with it being bright red.
speaker2: Lucky you!! Mine is just a plain brown.
speaker1: Sometimes wish it was plain, lots of questions asking if it's natural.
speaker2: True. People are mean sometimes. What do you like to do?
speaker1: Biking and hiking are two favorites. How about you?
speaker2: I like going to the ocean with my dog (a.k.a. My best friend) :).
speaker1: What kind of dog is it that you have?
speaker2: She's a cocker spaniel named Susie. She's fantastic and I love her.
speaker1: Aww she sounds so sweet! How old is she?
speaker2: About five years old. She's very friendly and smart. When it's time for walks, she gets her leash and brings it over. haha
speaker1: That's adorable! What part of the country are you in? Is it easy to walk her year-round?
speaker2: I live in the northeast, but I travel a lot. She's not a fan of the cold, but when I can travel to warmer areas, she comes with me. Do you have any pets?
speaker1: I've been thinking about getting a dog, but I have so much trouble making up my mind on what kind to get! What suggestions do you have?

speaker2: Well, it depends a lot on what you have in mind. When looking for a pet, think about things like: Will you have time to take care of them? If you have to travel, can they come with or do you have someone to look in on them? Do you want a quiet pet? Do you want a pet to play with? etc., etc. There's a lot to think about. I got my girl because she's easy to travel with and very friendly.
speaker1: I should probably think about getting a smaller breed, in all honesty. Have you ever owned a large dog?

speaker2: I have. My family had a golden retriever when I was young. He was a great dog. He's play with us out in the yard and go with us on walks around the block. He didn't like to be cooped up indoors, though. It's a good things we were very active kids. haha
speaker1: So what exactly do you do as an entrepreneur? What line of business are you in?
speaker2: I am in the dropshipping business, if you know what that entails?
speaker1: Hmm I'm not quite sure what is. Could you elaborate?

speaker2: So, I essentially act as a middle man between suppliers and distributers. I list products from them to a large audience, on a platform, and mark up the price because of my exposure to potential clients.
speaker1: Oh that makes sense! Do you enjoy your work? Does it require a lot of traveling?
speaker2: No, it is all remote, I never see the products, I just act as an advertiser really. It is very easy for the money it generates. Do you travel a lot?
speaker1: That sounds nice, seems like more down time from working remotely. I love to travel, I'm always trying to find new hiking spots
speaker2: Have you ever been to Scotland, they have some wonderful hiking spots!
speaker1: Yes! I actually did the west highland way hike. It was so beautiful! That trip made me want to adventure even more
speaker2: Have you heard of the North Coast 500?
speaker1: I think so- it's kind of like the Pacific Coast highway of Scotland right?
speaker2: Yes, you drive around for about 500 miles but there are hiking spots along the way. It is meant to be one of the most beautiful journeys ever!
speaker1: Could you give me some more information about getting started in dropshipping?

speaker2: Sure! Basically to get started in dropshipping, you just order goods from a distributer when the buyers are interested. You can make a lot of money in the middle ground with selling them for a higher price. Its kind of like flipping a home and making a profit. Are you interested in that job too?
speaker1: Maybe! I definitely need to find some creative ways to make money.  Someone told me the other day that they want to buy my hair, but I don't think that would be very steady work! haha
response: Oh wow! I've heard of people who like things like that. Maybe if you could sell it for a super high price, it would be worth it! I agree though, thats why I like remote work. These days its just not worth it for me to commute to a 9-5 everyday. Where do you work right now?
entities: I definitely need to find some creative ways to make money.  Someone told me the other day that they want to buy my hair, but I don't think that would be very steady work!
it is all remote

history: speaker1: Hello have you ever seen the show extreme couponing it’s my favorite.
speaker2: Yes I love that show really helps when you have lots of different food to buy.
speaker1: My coupon habit has let me buy food for all my animals and paint supplies.
speaker2: I love to read lots of books.
speaker1: Going to college full time sometimes makes it hard to get into a good book.
speaker2: That's true. What are your hobbies or other interests?
speaker1: Besides taking sunset walks I enjoy spending time with my 5 dogs and 3 rats.
speaker2: Sounds very interesting. I enjoy riding my bike.
speaker1: I could paint you riding your bike.
speaker2: That would be nice. Do you listen to music while painting?
speaker1: No I do not.
speaker2: Since your a student, if you need your computer fixed, I'm your guy.
speaker1: What books have you been recently recently then?
speaker2: I have been reading some classics, like To Kill a Mockingbird and The Great Gatsby. Have you read those?
speaker1: Yes! 3 of my dogs' names are Scout, Daisy, and Gatsby! Those are my absolute favorites.
speaker2: Wow that is amazing. They are some really well-written books. Have you seen the movies accompanying those books?
speaker1: I have. I liked both of the versions of The Great Gatsby. Did you like either the older or newer one better if you've seen them?
speaker2: I have seen both, but I have to go with the newer one. I think Leonardo Dicaprio is a terrific actor.

history: speaker1: Hello! Isn't it such a beautiful day out today!? How are you?
speaker2: Hello! Yes it is. I am very well, and you?
speaker1: I am great. Busy day, have lots of after school activities with my 3 kids today..
speaker2: Oh great! I have grandchildren. They are great and bring me joy..
speaker1: Yes, kids bring out the best in us!
speaker2: My family and friends are amazing and I love spending time with them.
speaker1: That is wonderful. I feel that way too, and about our furry family.
speaker2: I like to read. What is your favorite activity?
speaker1: I love farming. I live on one and enjoy tending to the earth!
speaker2: Wow thats great! I love god, and worshipping him!
speaker1: Do you work? My job deals with technology!
speaker2: All I do know is that I would like to live near water.
speaker1: How many grandchildren do you have now?
speaker2: I have 5, and they're the joy of my life! How old are your kids?
speaker1: 11. 9. and 7. I can't wait until their old enough to give me grandchildren of my own.
speaker2: It's amazing how quickly it happens! One day they're in diapers, the next they're off on their own! Cherish it while it lasts.
speaker1: I do, but It's never too early to plot revenge! lol When they have kids I'm gonna fill them up with sugar and send them home to torture my kids! lol
speaker2: Haha you've got quite the imagination! I forget just how much trouble those little ones can get into. Try to stay sane!
speaker1: My kids are pretty good and I love them. They get pretty rambunctious at times though.  Always accidentally trampling over crops.
speaker2: It must be a lot of fun raising kids on a farm, though! What's the major crop you all produce?
speaker1: Tomatoes which I've genetically engineered.
speaker2: Wow, so you've got a green thumb, and you're tech savvy! I'm impressed!
speaker1: Well, my husband does most of the growing.  I just work on new breeds of crops that are resistant to trampling!
speaker2: Haha if you can patent that, you'll be a very wealthy lady!
speaker1: Do all of your kids have children of their own?

speaker2: I have three children myself, though my grandkids are from my two eldest children. My youngest child doesn't have any, and to be honest they've said they don't want children anyway. Would you like to have grandchildren one day?
speaker1: Oh definitely! I have three kids of my own and can't wait to have grandkids. Mine are still young though.
speaker2: Ah yes of course. How are they getting on at school? My youngest grandchild starts school this year.
speaker1: They love it. We started the year going 5 days a week. I can't believe kids are still virtual or even hybrid. As a teacher I feel strongly that these kids need to be in school fulltime.
response: Yes it must have been so hard on chlidren having to learn remotely. One of the most important parts of school is being together with other children. What age group do you teach?
entities: I can't believe kids are still virtual or even hybrid. As a teacher I feel strongly that these kids need to be in school fulltime.

history: speaker1: How have you been?!
speaker2: Im good, how are you doing?
speaker1: I'm great! Moving this month to my favorite area!
speaker2: Sounds amazing. Laying in bed sick grading papers, I teach english to high school students.
speaker1: Is it just a cold, or something worse?!
speaker2: It is a cold. I went for a walk in the rain at the park yesterday.
speaker1: Ah, I know school can be strict on absences. Mine was.
speaker2: I bet, I was always absence when I was in school.
speaker1: My dad was headmaster, so I couldn't get away with it.
speaker2: Yikes, that doesn't sound fun. Do you have any hobbies?
speaker1: Just watching the bears and eating deep dish pizza! Yourself?
speaker2: That sounds like fun. I volunteer at a soup kitchen every two weeks.
speaker1: A teacher and a volunteer! Gosh, my older siblings are right about me...
speaker2: When I'm not volunteering I work on sketching landscape scenery.
speaker1: How do you like teaching high school students?
speaker2: I love it. It can be frustrating but always worth it.Plus got to love summers off. Did your dad like working with kids?
speaker1: He did, but he was very strict. He would say he was helping develop the leaders of tomorrow.
speaker2: What was like having him at school with you? Did kids give you a hard time?

speaker1: haha Yes, they very much did. They would say my good grades were because of my dad, not my hard work. I think my dad gave me the hardest time, though. It was tough because he could look at my grades and talk to my teachers.
speaker2: I imagine you never got to get away with anything. How is your move going?

speaker1: It's pretty good! I've gotten some things boxed, but most things sorted. A couple friends are coming over this weekend. We're going to grab some pizza and make a day of it. You're welcome to come, if you want.
speaker2: Haha Moving is my least favorite activity. I'm so bad about packing it makes me anxious. I'd probably be more of a hassle then helpful
speaker1: That's okay! So, what are your plans for this weekend? Anything exciting?
speaker2: This is my weekend for volunteering at the soup kitchen.
speaker1: That's very cool! I've always wanted to do that. Maybe I can join you sometime after this move gets sorted.
speaker2: Yea! Any time you can join everyone would appreciate it. Do you cook at all?
speaker1: My dad told me he is planning to visit one I get all moved in.
speaker2: Oh my! That is good, right? Or does it just make you nervous?

speaker1: It is not exciting. He is a lot to handle. I need to start volunteering soon so I can always have an excuse to get out of the house. Can I start at your soup kitchen in the next couple of weeks?
response: We are always looking for help. I am sure they will be happy to have you any weekend, but if you want to join me, I will be there the weekend after next. I can train you, but I have no doubt it will be a breeze for you. Sorry your dad makes you feel that way. It may be different now that he will be on your territory.
